PV commands

#pvdisplay  - display information
#pvs - display information
#pvscan - scans for disks for non-LVM and LVM disks 
#pvcreate  - Create physical volume
#pvremove - remove physical volume
#pvck - check the consistency of the LVM metadata 
#pvchange - Enable or Disable PV
#pvmove  - move data from harddisk to second disk

VG commands

#vgdisplay - display information
#vgs - display information
#vgscan - scanning
#vgcreate - create volume group
#vgremove - remove volume group
#vgreduce - reduce volume group / removing disk from VG
#vgchk - check the consistency of the LVM metadata 
#vgchange - Enable or Disable VG
#vgrename - rename VG
#vgconvert  - convert LVM1 to LVM2
#vgexport
#vgimport
#vgcfgbackup - the backup is written in plain text and are by default located in /etc/lvm/backup 

LV commands

#lvdisplay  - display information
#lvs - display information
#lvscan - scans for lvs 
#lvcreate  - Create logical volume
#lvremove - remove logical volume
#lvextend - extend LV
#lvreduce - reduce LV
#lvrename - rename LV

Directories and Files

## Directories
/etc/lvm                    - default lvm directory location 
/etc/lvm/backup         - where the automatic backups go 
/etc/lvm/cache          - persistent filter cache 
/etc/lvm/archive        - where automatic archives go after a volume group change 
/var/lock/lvm             - lock files to prevent metadata corruption 

# Files 
/etc/lvm/lvm.conf       - main lvm configuration file 
$HOME/.lvm               - lvm history


